<p>The star seems to be on a selling spree. In January, the siren sold a large home in Calabasas, California for $6.6M. </p>

<p>These days she is settled into her old Petty house where Stevie Nicks used to hang out.</p>

<p>Her new digs: This comes months after the Monte Carlo star snapped up the late rocker Tom Petty's former home in Encino, California, for $4.9 million (pictured)</p>

<p>The Wolves singer splashed out the eye-watering sum of money on the mansion Tom and his ex-wife Jane Benyo designed back in 1989. </p>

<p>The property has since been renovated. The I Won't Back Down singer from Florida died in 2017 at the age of 66 at his Malibu mansion.</p>

<p>The 11,000 square foot property boasts six bedrooms and 10 baths, according to E! News, which reports that it also features plenty of spare rooms suitable for leisure activities.</p>
